%N A392441 a(n) is the sum of n consecutive triangular numbers immediately preceding a triangular number T(k), which is also equal to the sum of n-1 consecutive triangular numbers immediately following T(k).
%C A392441 There exists only one such k and it is equal to 2*n^2-1.
%C A392441 Sequence has a lot of similar properties to A222716.
%H A392441 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A392441/b392441.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A392441 <a href="/index/Rec#order_06">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (6,-15,20,-15,6,-1).
%F A392441 a(n) = T(k-n) + ... + T(k-1) = T(k+1) + ... + T(k+n-1), where k = 2*n^2-1 and T = A000217.
%F A392441 a(n) = n*(n - 1)*(12*n^3 + 6*n^2 - 5*n - 2)/6.
%F A392441 From _Stefano Spezia_, Jan 19 2026: (Start)
%F A392441 G.f.: x^2*(36 + 145*x + 58*x^2 + x^3)/(1 - x)^6.
%F A392441 E.g.f.: exp(x)*x^2*(108 + 253*x + 114*x^2 + 12*x^3)/6. (End)
%e A392441 For n = 3, k = 17 and the triangular numbers preceding and following that index are
%e A392441                           k
%e A392441   i    =  14   15   16   17   18   19
%e A392441   T(i) = 105, 120, 136, 153, 171, 190
%e A392441          \-----------/       \------/
%e A392441   a(n) =      361         =    361
%t A392441 A392441[n_] := n*(n - 1)*(12*n^3 + 6*n^2 - 5*n - 2)/6;
